```json
{
"application": "DeepLabV3+",
"software_requirements": [
"Python",
"PyTorch",
"MMSegmentation",
"CUDA",
"nvidia-smi",
"slurm"
],
"resource_requirements": {
"cpus": 2,
"gpu": 1,
"memory": "32GB",
"time": "7 days"
}
}
```

The script runs a DeepLabV3+ model for semantic segmentation. It leverages the MMSegmentation framework, requiring Python, PyTorch, and CUDA for execution. The script utilizes the slurm workload manager, requesting 2 CPUs, 1 GPU, 32GB of memory, and a runtime of 7 days. It also includes functionalities to check for existing results and use them to resume training or perform testing.
